ESWITCH v0.3 - Switch between EGA and Tandy Video II
----------------------------------------------------

Based on VSWITCH by Jeffrey L. Hayes.
Please see VSWITCH.DOC for further information.

Requirements: a Tandy 1000 with 768k and Tandy Video II (TL and later)
              an EGA card

Usage: ESRES (install resident portion)
       ESWITCH (switch between EGA and Tandy video)
       
An EGA daughterboard can be used to route Tandy video to the EGA output,
allowing a single monitor to be used.
See https://github.com/bjt42/eswitch/wiki for a circuit diagram.

Questions? Get in touch with bjt on vogons.org or the Vintage Computer Forums.
